00:13.716 --> 00:14.349
Hey.

00:14.373 --> 00:15.571
Hey.

00:15.572 --> 00:16.804
Closed door?

00:16.806 --> 00:19.039
I want to talk to you.

00:19.041 --> 00:20.608
Talk to or talk at?

00:20.610 --> 00:21.942
Probably nothing.

00:21.944 --> 00:24.078
Well, maybe nothing.
So something.

00:24.080 --> 00:26.480
Got a call from one of
our COs this morning.

00:26.482 --> 00:28.749
Turns out one of our cops
got his nose broken

00:28.751 --> 00:30.951
busting up a bar fight
on the upper east side.

00:30.953 --> 00:32.152
Okay, that happened.

00:32.154 --> 00:34.154
Thing is, the perp
in the incident

00:34.156 --> 00:36.223
is Alex Jasper.
Not ringing a bell.

00:36.225 --> 00:38.058
Son of Frederick T. Jasper.

00:38.060 --> 00:40.027
The mayor's main bundler?
The same.

00:40.029 --> 00:40.860
Oh.

00:40.884 --> 00:42.396
Normally, you
hit a cop,

00:42.397 --> 00:43.630
you break his nose,

00:43.632 --> 00:45.532
the judge hits you
with a hefty bail.

00:45.534 --> 00:46.766
I'm guessing that
didn't happen here.

00:46.768 --> 00:48.501
Released on his
own recognizance.

00:48.503 --> 00:49.802
I see.

00:49.804 --> 00:51.504
And this comes
to me because...

00:51.506 --> 00:53.039
Because should we
tell the boss?

00:53.041 --> 00:54.941
We?

00:54.943 --> 00:56.976
Well, now that you know
the particulars, yeah.

00:56.978 --> 01:00.513
Crafty. Two minutes ago
I was blissfully ignorant.

01:00.515 --> 01:01.781
Should we tell the boss?

01:01.783 --> 01:02.782
Is there any evidence that says

01:02.784 --> 01:04.617
the mayor talked
to that judge?

01:04.619 --> 01:05.918
Well, no, but it's
pretty obvious

01:05.920 --> 01:06.953
what's going on here.

01:06.955 --> 01:09.288
We don't say anything
to Frank

01:09.290 --> 01:10.456
until there's something to say.

01:10.458 --> 01:12.158
Are you sure?

01:17.698 --> 01:18.664
Morning.

01:18.666 --> 01:20.466
Hey, Danny.
Morning.

01:20.468 --> 01:21.734
- Morning, Regan.
- Morning.

01:21.736 --> 01:22.485
I got to tell him?

01:22.509 --> 01:23.803
You're the one
bringing it here.

01:23.804 --> 01:25.537
He's always pissed
about something.

01:25.539 --> 01:27.038
Get ready.
Heard 'em talking

01:27.040 --> 01:28.774
about a double
homicide came in.

01:28.776 --> 01:30.276
You mean the one they just gave
to Byrne and Bitterman?

01:30.278 --> 01:31.910
They're not gonna give
it to those bananas

01:31.912 --> 01:34.012
while we're sitting around
twiddling our thumbs.

01:34.014 --> 01:35.546
Well, we're no longer twiddling.

01:36.316 --> 01:38.349
Who's this,
and why is his foot

01:38.351 --> 01:40.418
on the furniture?

01:40.420 --> 01:42.087
Officer Mahoney.
How you doing?

01:42.089 --> 01:43.155
Just came off this job.

01:43.157 --> 01:44.322
- Sarge said to give it to you.
- What is it?

01:44.324 --> 01:46.324
Teen suicide.
You got to be kidding me.

01:46.326 --> 01:47.286
It's busy work.

01:47.310 --> 01:48.795
Hey, I'm just
the messenger.

01:48.796 --> 01:50.796
You're not just the messenger.
You're first on the scene, right?

01:50.798 --> 01:53.798
What do you know about
this Derrick Madigan kid?

01:53.800 --> 01:55.966
He's a good kid, just got
mixed up with the wrong crowd.

01:55.968 --> 01:58.202
What's that got to do with him
taking his own life?

01:58.204 --> 02:00.204
I think he got
peer-pressured by his friends.

02:00.206 --> 02:01.806
He was a lookout for one of
their robberies the other night.

02:01.808 --> 02:04.108
Once he heard we caught
wind of his involvement,

02:04.110 --> 02:05.410
well, word on
the street is

02:05.412 --> 02:06.877
he panicked.

02:06.879 --> 02:08.745
How'd he do it?

02:08.747 --> 02:11.548
His mother found him handing
by his belt in the closet.

02:11.550 --> 02:13.217
Oh, good Lord.

02:13.219 --> 02:15.152
As you can imagine, she ain't
doing so good right about now.

02:15.154 --> 02:16.787
Yeah, I wouldn't think so.

02:17.924 --> 02:19.957
So, uh, what can I
tell the boss?

02:19.959 --> 02:21.292
Tell the boss
we'll take the case

02:21.294 --> 02:23.794
and to teach you
some manners.

02:23.796 --> 02:25.495
Again with the foot!

02:27.098 --> 02:28.064
All right.
Yeah, all right.

02:28.066 --> 02:29.433
We got it from
here, good-bye.

02:31.036 --> 02:32.369
It was all you,
Your Majesty.

02:32.371 --> 02:34.871
Come on, we're a team.
When I win, you win.

02:34.873 --> 02:37.207
I just happen
to win more often.

02:37.209 --> 02:39.576
Funny thing is,
you ain't kidding.

02:39.578 --> 02:41.577
Oh, come on,
of course I am.

02:41.579 --> 02:42.678
You know that.

02:42.680 --> 02:45.181
There's a Reggie Wilson
here to see you.

02:45.183 --> 02:46.782
I don't see him
on your schedule.

02:46.784 --> 02:48.584
Reggie Wilson?
Sounds familiar.

02:48.586 --> 02:51.454
Wasn't he our
sole eyewitness

02:51.456 --> 02:52.956
on that homicide last year?

02:52.958 --> 02:54.991
Yeah, you're right.
He took the stand for us

02:54.993 --> 02:58.026
when the neighborhood
wouldn't even look our way.

02:58.028 --> 03:00.062
So I should let him in?
Please.

03:00.064 --> 03:01.797
He's got big stones,
this guy.

03:01.799 --> 03:04.767
By “stones” you're meaning
his intestinal fortitude?

03:04.769 --> 03:06.502
Sure. Whatever.

03:06.504 --> 03:08.671
Mr. Wilson.

03:08.673 --> 03:10.973
Miss Erin,
the pleasure's mine.

03:10.975 --> 03:12.908
Nice to see you.
Good to see you.

03:12.910 --> 03:14.376
Reggie, how are you?
Anthony, right?

03:14.378 --> 03:15.477
Look like you lost
some weight.

03:15.479 --> 03:18.113
I'll find it soon enough.

03:18.115 --> 03:19.848
So what brings you
all the way down here

03:19.850 --> 03:21.516
from the Bronx?

03:21.518 --> 03:23.418
I'm gonna be
straight with you.

03:23.420 --> 03:25.653
The way I see it,
I helped you out pretty good

03:25.655 --> 03:27.455
on that situation
you had last year.

03:28.458 --> 03:30.759
You did your civic duty,
for which we're grateful,

03:30.761 --> 03:31.793
if that's what you mean.

03:31.795 --> 03:33.428
Now it's your turn.

03:33.430 --> 03:34.962
My turn?

03:34.964 --> 03:37.164
It's your turn
to scratch my back.

03:42.906 --> 03:44.205
The dream team, sir.

03:45.709 --> 03:47.241
- Morning.
- Morning.

03:47.243 --> 03:48.575
How's it going, boss?
It's going.

03:48.577 --> 03:49.944
You see that piece
in the news?

03:49.946 --> 03:51.412
Nice little pat
on the back.

03:51.414 --> 03:53.781
In the neighborhood section,
page after the comics.

03:53.783 --> 03:55.616
Well, okay.

03:55.618 --> 03:57.684
I spoke to the Chief of D's,
like you asked.

03:57.686 --> 03:59.320
He says you're gonna
be very happy

03:59.322 --> 04:00.922
about this month's numbers.

04:00.924 --> 04:03.757
And you're personally
guaranteeing it?

04:03.759 --> 04:05.626
Well, no, I just...

04:05.628 --> 04:08.529
Better to under-promise
than over-deliver.

04:09.398 --> 04:11.264
Well, that's a good one.

04:13.368 --> 04:17.036
And what about
the Jasper kid's ROR?

04:21.276 --> 04:24.710
ROR, as in released
on own recognizance?

04:24.712 --> 04:26.112
As in no bail.

04:26.114 --> 04:27.247
I know what it means, sir.

04:27.249 --> 04:29.282
So you know about it, right?
Yeah.

04:29.284 --> 04:31.418
Yes, we just didn't know
you did.

04:31.420 --> 04:35.088
And you were about to tell me?
Because it's not in here.

04:35.090 --> 04:37.122
Well...
Look, I have dinner

04:37.124 --> 04:40.292
every Sunday with
the former PC, a detective,

04:40.294 --> 04:41.994
a beat cop, and an A.D.A.

04:41.996 --> 04:44.096
Did you really think
all my Intel

04:44.098 --> 04:45.197
flowed through you two?

04:45.199 --> 04:46.933
No, but...
I also charter

04:46.935 --> 04:50.202
a boat out of Montauk
from time to time

04:50.204 --> 04:52.839
with Officer Broken Nose's CO.

04:52.841 --> 04:57.142
Call in some chips and get
the presiding judge's phone log,

04:57.144 --> 05:00.112
and see who reached out.

05:00.114 --> 05:01.947
Now would be a good time.

